                     <msItem xml:id="p2_i1">
                        <locus from="3ra" to="12v"/>
                       <title type="incomplete">A lexicon for <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3942Ezekiel">the Book of Ezekiel</ref> (ነገረ፡ ሕዝቅኤል፡) followed by 
                         the Interpretation of the Sanctuary (ትርጓሜ፡ መቅደስ፡ ዘሕዝቅኤል፡), incomplete</title>
                      <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez"><supplied reason="undefined" resp="DN">ነገ</supplied>ረ፡ ሕዝቅኤል፡ ኅብረ፡</incipit>
                       <explicit xml:lang="gez"/>
                       
                        <note>The paper guard covers the beginning of the lines on 
                           <locus target="#3ra"/>. Written by several hands, the leaves are probably in disorder. 
                           <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/XQXTC5KU"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Cowley1988Exeget"/><title level="m">Ethiopian Biblical Interpretation: A Study in Exegetical Tradition and Hermeneutics</title><title level="s">University of Cambridge Oriental Publications</title><author><forename>Roger W.</forename><surname>Cowley</surname></author><pubPlace>Cambridge</pubPlace><publisher>Cambridge University Press</publisher><date>1988</date><series><title level="s">University of Cambridge Oriental Publications</title><biblScope unit="volume">38</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">38</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Bible</note><note type="tag">Commentary</note><note type="tag">bm:Cowley1988Exeget</note></note><note type="tag">Bible</note><note type="tag">Commentary</note><note type="tag">bm:Cowley1988Exeget</note><citedRange unit="page">461</citedRange></bibl> indicates, without further remarks, that the same text appears in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML1279">Collegeville, Hill Museum and Manuscript Library, MS EMML no. 1279</ref>, 
                         but it cannot be ascertained for the moment. The text seems to be different from a lexicon on Ezekiel contained in 
                           <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML1292">Addis Ababa, የኢትዮጵያ፡ ጤናትና፡ ምርምር፡ ተቋም፡, MS 19</ref>.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msContents>

